  "order": "r || s || v with v in {27, 28}; the on-chain decoder accepts exactly 65 bytes. compact_2098 is RecoverableSignature's ERC-2098 form (r || vs with y_parity in bit 255 of vs): encoding normalizes s to low-s first (alloy as_erc2098), so a high-s input round-trips to its canonical low-s twin — the same (digest, signer) validity under ECDSA malleability — and canonical_packed_signature is that twin's 65-byte form.",
